main event: An unidentified aerial object was observed in Huntington, California on April 1, 1956.
interesting points: The object was a bright-white, oval shape and was very small,The sighting lasted for thirty minutes at an altitude of 5,000 feet,The object moved westwardly at erratic speeds,10 conclusions were drawn regarding the nature of the object, including possibilities of being a balloon, aircraft, or astronomical phenomenon,The report noted characteristic similarities to a satellite observed in the same position.
witness description: no witnesses confirmed in the report
